  "Simple random sampling": "",
  "Stratified sampling": "",
  "Voluntary response sampling": "",
  "Convenience sampling": "",
  "Because a random sample is drawn from each stratum, stratified sampling guarantees that every important subgroup is represented.": "",
  "Cluster sampling is most cost-effective when the population is:": "",
  "Small and accessible": "",
  "Already listed alphabetically": "",
  "Geographically spread out": "",
  "Completely homogeneous": "",
  "Sampling entire clusters in a few locations reduces travel and administrative costs when the population is widely dispersed.": "",
  "Selecting every 10th person on a list is an example of:": "",
  "Systematic sampling": "",
  "Cluster sampling": "",
  "Using a fixed interval (every 10th person) after a random start is the hallmark of systematic sampling.": "",
  "Which of the following is NOT a probability sampling method?": "",
  "SRS": "",
  "Convenience sampling does not use random selection, so it is a non-probability method and cannot support valid statistical inference.": "",
